## ðŸ›  Setup Instructions

### 1. Install MongoDB
You can either:
- **Install MongoDB locally**: [Download MongoDB Community Edition](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community)  
- **Or use MongoDB Atlas**: [Create a free cluster](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas)

Make sure MongoDB is running before proceeding.

---

### 2. Insert Sample Books
1. Open **PowerShell** or terminal.  
2. Start Mongo shell:
```powershell
mongosh

3.Switch to the database:
use plp_bookstore
4.Copy and paste the content of insert_books.js into the shell.
5.Press Enter.
6.Verify the data was inserted:
     db.books.find().pretty()
